      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Historians overwhelmingly agree that the UN is fundamentally structured to reflect the geopolitical realities of the post-WWII era, which inherently favors the great powers. The veto power held by the Security Council's permanent members is the clearest evidence that the organization is not a truly neutral arbiter. Therefore, the criticism that it serves the interests of the powerful is not fringe; it is a central, well-supported critique of the system's design.",
      "source": "target",
